ss 18w36g1">;.css-18w36g1{width:100%;font-family:var(--ds-type-system-sans); }</style>;<figcaption class="css-18w36g1 emlhmni2">;<style data-emotion="css 10r7phw">;.css-10r7phw{font-family:var(--ds-type-system-sans);font -size:var(--ds-type-scale--1);font-weight:400;font-variant:small-caps no-common-ligatures no-discretionary-ligatures no-historical-ligatures no-contextual;line -高度:var(--ds-type-leading-lower);文本变换:小写;颜色:var(--ds-color-london-35);}.emlhmni0+.css-10r7phw{margin-left:0.25 rem;}</style>;<span class="css-10r7phw emlhmni1">;地图：《经济学人》</span>;</figcaption>;</figure>;</div>;<p data-component="paragraph" class=" css-1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0">;相反，冲突已经转移到<a href="https://www.economist.com/leaders/2023/11/16/the-world-is-ignoring-war-genocide-and-苏丹的饥荒“全国性的大火</a>;如此巨大和无政府状态，可能会破坏苏丹的几个邻国的稳定。 If there were, at first, two broadly coherent armed blocs under identifiable leadership, now there is a mosaic of competing militias and rebel movements, each with their own interests and agendas. At the same time, arms and mercenaries are pouring over the border from Chad, Libya and the Central African Republic, and across the Red Sea. Even fighters from as far afield as Russia and Ukraine have reportedly joined the fray.由于双方都未能给予决定性的打击，<small>;新加坡武装部队</small>;和<small>;RSF</small>;都开始分裂。 “我们正朝着一个失败的国家飞速前进，”美国最近任命的特使汤姆·佩里洛 (Tom Perriello) 忧心忡忡地说道。 “苏丹和更广泛地区的人民确实面临着 20 至 25 年倒退的风险。”</p>;<div class="adComponent_advert__kPVUI adComponent_incontent__boSCu adComponent_hidden_​​_Dp0GM css-0 e1cbnkh80">;<div>;<div id ="econ-1" class="adComponent_adcontainer__eooQr">;</div>;</div>;</div>;<p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0">;更直接的是大规模饥饿的风险。荷兰智库 Clingendael Institute 的一项研究显示，“最有可能发生的情况”预计，到 6 月，苏丹大部分地区将遭遇饥荒，造成 50 万人死亡。在其“极端”情景预测中，多达一百万人可能死亡。由于战争，苏丹大部分地区（尤其是达尔富尔）在 2023 年几乎没有收成。全国谷物产量几乎下降了一半； the price of basic food commodities shot up by as much as 83%.随着战斗现已蔓延到杰齐拉的粮仓州，这些趋势将会恶化。</p>;<p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0">;尽管<small>;联合国</small>;已经尽管尚未正式宣布进入饥荒，但很少有专家怀疑苏丹部分地区已经开始出现饥荒。在包括首都在内的受影响最严重的地区，人们靠吃树叶来生存。 Children are already beginning to die from malnutrition or related diseases.援助组织 <small>;CARE</small>; 的 Deepmala Mahla 表示，受战争影响地区约 70% 的医疗设施已无法使用。去年大部分时间里，抵达与西达尔富尔州接壤的乍得的难民表示，他们正在逃避无国界医生部队和阿拉伯联盟民兵针对当地非洲黑人发动的可怕种族清洗运动。现在，新来者告诉救援人员，他们是为了逃离饥饿。</p>;<p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0">;战争双方都在阻碍人道主义援助。 <small>;RSF</small>;战士经常袭击属于<small>;NGO</small>;的援助卡车和战利品仓库。二月份，<small>;苏丹武装部队</small>;禁止援助机构通过乍得运送物资。 Since then it has partially relented, but it continues to withhold visas and travel permits for aid workers.一位<small>;联合国</small>;官员指出，跨越<small>;新加坡武装部队</small>;和<small>;RSF</small>;控制的领土之间的界限来提供援助是“麻烦且故意耗时的” 。 As a result, whole regions have for months been cut off from emergency supplies. “Previous food crises in Sudan were localised,” argues Alex de Waal, an expert on famines at Tufts University. “现在我们正在目睹自 19 世纪以来从未见过的事情：全国范围内的粮食紧急情况。”</p>;<div class="adComponent_advert__kPVUI adComponent_incontent__boSCu adComponent_hidden_​​_Dp0GM css-0 e1cbnkh80">;<div>;<div id="econ- 2" class="adComponent_adcontainer__eooQr">;</div>;</div>;</div>;<p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0">;考虑一下北达尔富尔州首府法希尔和<小>;新加坡武装部队</small>;在西部的最后一个主要据点。 Before the war, the city was a sanctuary for those escaping violence and hunger elsewhere: tens, if not hundreds, of thousands of civilians had sheltered there since the previous round of ethnic cleansing in Darfur 20 years ago. Yet these days it is a microcosm of the chaos that prevails elsewhere in Sudan. In theory, the national army remains in charge, with several thousand troops holed up in barracks in the city centre.但实际上，当地扎格哈瓦族的叛乱分子提供了大部分安全保障，而郊区的大部分地区则处于<small>;RSF</small>;及其附属民兵的控制之下。 Crossing from one side of the city to the other means navigating multiple checkpoints, each manned by different armed groups.尽管军队经常对<small>;无国界支援部队</small>;阵地进行空袭，但最终往往会袭击平民地区，包括自己控制下的地区。</p>;<p data-component="paragraph" class="css -1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0">;由于法希尔进出和周围的活动成本如此之高且危险，里面的生活变得越来越绝望。 “我们已经太晚了，”法国人道主义慈善机构国际团结组织的贾斯汀·穆齐克 (Justine Muzik) 说。登革热和疟疾正在猖獗。另一家法国慈善机构无国界医生组织表示，在西南部的扎姆扎姆难民营，每两个小时就会有一名儿童因缺乏食物或医疗护理而死亡。随着新移民从达尔富尔其他地区涌入该市，基本物资正在减少。尽管市场上仍然可以买到食物，但价格却贵得离谱：一袋大米的价格几乎是战前的八倍。</p>;<p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0 “在该国大部分地区，双方士兵都在强奸妇女和女孩，有时是因为她们的种族。 In Khartoum state alone more than 1,000 rapes have taken place, according to lawyers and doctors. Ghada Abbas, a human rights lawyer who recently fled Sudan, describes an incident in which soldiers violated three sisters aged 12, 16 and 18 in Omdurman, a city close to the capital.她说，虽然人们听到了他们的哭声，但“没有人敢出去”。</p>;<p data-component="paragraph" class="css-1f0x4sl e1tt35bk0">;其他地方也出现了一些充满希望的迹象。 Discreet ceasefire talks between the two sides are under way in the Egyptian capital, Cairo. A separate process backed by America is also to resume in Saudi Arabia soon. Meanwhile donors are meeting in Paris on April 15th in the hope of drumming up more funds for humanitarian efforts.然而，最近几周，军队扭转了<small>;RSF</small>;早些时候在喀土穆取得的一些成果，为其支持者带来了决定性胜利的希望。就在几周前，<small>;RSF</small>;还取得了胜利。 “What this looks like now is musical chairs,” not a genuine sea-change, argues Kholood Khair of Confluence Advisory, a Sudanese think-tank.由于双方仍决心占据上风，和平前景渺茫。 <span class="ufinish">;■</span>;</p>;</div>; https://www.economist.com/middle-east-and-africa/2024/04/15/after-one-year-of-war-sudan-is-a-failing-state /内容/1phuiqfqvmcpbfhff3fdasa735iccdea Mon, 15 Apr 2024 17:11:18 GMT
